  "texts": [
    "In the task of HPE, the Average Precision (AP) metric based on OKS is widely used to evaluate algorithm performance.",
    "The AP metric calculates the average precision based on different thresholds and object sizes.",
    "For example, AP50 represents the average precision at an OKS threshold of 50, while AP75 represents the average precision at an OKS threshold of 75.",
    "To assess the performance of pose estimation for persons of different scales, the COCO dataset provides additional metrics.",
    "A P M (AP for medium objects: 3 2 2 < area < 96 2) represents the average precision for medium-sized objects, and A P L (AP for large objects: a rea > 96 2) represents the average precision for larger objects."
  ],
